"\nBOWS"
"\n"
"\nThe Yokudans had little esteem for archery, deeming it less honorable than melee combat, and their gallants and grandees left it to the common foot soldier. A Yokudan archer or light skirmisher was usually armed with a simple self bow adorned with modest metal facings."
msgstr "シーカーの公文書保管人、イブルーラ著\\r"
"\n\\r"
